  "title": "For the Good of Caspar",
  "summary": "Over wine and light fare at the exclusive Captain's Table restaurant in Noques Rasala, Presav Crestian Tarasar and Grand Inquisitor Axel Vichten share a private dinner meeting to take stock of the fragile Imperium and the future of Caspar. They discuss the embarrassment of a recent prison breakout, the prolonged absence of the Sith Lord Malign, and the security of Selene against potential sabotage by Malus and his dark adepts. Much of their conversation turns to their mutual friend Lynae Cassius, whose deepening alliance with Malign and obsessive research into removing the Force from future generations forced her resignation from the Navy and the withdrawal of her son Andrev from the academy. The two leaders trade candid reflections on their own pasts, their pragmatic rather than loyal relationships with Malign, and Axel's intelligence network, including the spy Ssanyu. The meeting closes on a note of hard-won mutual respect, with both men committing to protecting the Union and weathering whatever galactic collapse may come, before Axel departs and leaves the bill on his tab.",
